- if @user.errors.any?
  .alert.alert-error

    %p
      I'm sorry I couldn't save it because...
      %ul
      - @user.errors.messages.each do |message|
        %li
          = message.first
          = message.last.last


%h1 
  Get Yours
  %small 
    Snag your own booksmartlet. 

.row-fluid
  .span7
    .well
      %h2 Sign Up...
      = form_for @user do |user|
        .control-group
          .controls
            = user.text_field :email, :placeholder => 'Enter your email'
        .control-group
          .controls
            = user.password_field :password, :placeholder => 'Choose a password'
        .form-actions
          %input.btn.btn-info.btn-large{:type => 'submit', :value => 'Create'}
          &nbsp;
          or
          &nbsp;
          %a{:href => new_login_path} Cancel

  .span5
    .well
      %h2 What is this?
      %p
        Booksmartlet is really simple. We just generate a bookmarklet with a token.
        %strong
          Here is all you need to do.
        %ul
          %li Supply an email and a password
          %li we will generate an API key for your booksmartlet
          %li Drag the link to your bookmark bar, and use

